  pages={143-148},
  abstract={The medical applications of artificial intelligence techniques more people in today's culture are afflicted with chronic illnesses. They are the primary global cause of death. However, as the global population ages, the necessity for health care is becoming increasingly pressing. Prominent global players in the health sector have acknowledged the significance of creating advanced medical services. Massive volumes of intricate patient data must be collected in order to construct a wide range of intelligent decision support systems. To help doctors and caregivers prescribe appropriate treatment for patients' well-being, data should be appropriately gathered, processed, and presented. Personalized healthcare and medicine are the main emphasis of contemporary methods to do this. It is also beneficial to include e-coaching tools assisted by agents and metaverse technology in such systems. Globally, artificial intelligence (AI)applications are growing in popularity. In the field of medicine, "machine learning"-based devices are becoming widely accessible, especially for image processing. The application of AI in healthcare is anticipated to increase due to the industry's growing complexity and volume of data. Various forms of artificial intelligence are currently being used. Healthcare technology innovation is greatly aided by the field of instrumentation and measurement system.A broad platform that aids in streamlining the numerous tasks and exchanges that occur on a daily basis in the healthcare sector is healthcare software development. It makes it simple and safe to exchange and store patient data.},
